window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Hugo Award winner Harry Turtledove is the master of alternate history. In <i>American Front</i> he envisions World War I as it may have been if fought on American soil. The United States and Germany clash with the Confederacy, France, and Britain as the machines of modern warfare litter the landscape with carnage. Meanwhile, oppressed southern blacks head toward a fateful confrontation. </p>"; 
